1:17:56.231 --> 1:17:58.898
circle up, circle up, circle up.

1:18:00.082 --> 1:18:01.490
Alright, this is it, guys,

1:18:01.490 --> 1:18:04.730
three outs, right, we
hold them for three outs,

1:18:04.730 --> 1:18:06.180
we're state champions.

1:18:06.180 --> 1:18:07.013
You gonna do this?

1:18:07.013 --> 1:18:08.048
- [Players] Yeah!

1:18:08.048 --> 1:18:09.138
- You gonna shut them down?

1:18:09.138 --> 1:18:11.190
- [Players] Yeah!

1:18:11.190 --> 1:18:14.033
- You do this, this memory
will last a lifetime.

1:18:15.090 --> 1:18:16.367
Take us out, Kyle.

1:18:16.367 --> 1:18:17.662
- [Kyle] Brighton on three,

1:18:17.662 --> 1:18:21.191
- [All] One, two, three, Brighton!

1:18:21.191 --> 1:18:23.892
- [John] Alright, guys,
let's go, this is it.

1:18:23.892 --> 1:18:28.059
- [Announcer] Now batting,
number 24, Damien Hall.

1:18:32.063 --> 1:18:36.896
(groans)
(audience gasps)

1:18:38.205 --> 1:18:39.270
- You alright, buddy?

1:18:39.270 --> 1:18:40.698
- Where'd that get you?
- Where'd it hit you?

1:18:40.698 --> 1:18:41.670
- My knee.

1:18:41.670 --> 1:18:42.963
- Can you get up?
- Can you stand?

1:18:44.140 --> 1:18:45.563
- One, two, three, yeah.

1:18:46.644 --> 1:18:47.690
You did great.

1:18:47.690 --> 1:18:49.370
- How many did Ricky throw yesterday?

1:18:49.370 --> 1:18:51.143
- 70, he can't go.

1:18:52.380 --> 1:18:53.213
- [John] You alright?

1:18:53.213 --> 1:18:54.987
- [Troy] Let me help you, buddy.

1:18:56.410 --> 1:18:57.890
- Tommy!

1:18:57.890 --> 1:18:58.723
- Coach.

1:19:02.400 --> 1:19:03.233
Can I pitch?

1:19:05.222 --> 1:19:06.080
- I thought you'd never ask, buddy.

1:19:06.080 --> 1:19:08.060
I thought you'd never ask.

1:19:08.060 --> 1:19:09.180
Head back on out.

1:19:09.180 --> 1:19:10.680
Brandon!

1:19:10.680 --> 1:19:11.563
Take short!

1:19:12.450 --> 1:19:14.170
- Have you seen him throw?

1:19:14.170 --> 1:19:15.970
- I heard he's never pitched before.

1:19:17.240 --> 1:19:18.073
- Really?

1:19:21.100 --> 1:19:21.933
- Kyle, don't worry,

1:19:21.933 --> 1:19:24.490
just stare at the glove

1:19:24.490 --> 1:19:26.367
and just throw like you're
playing catch, alright?

1:19:26.367 --> 1:19:27.640
And you don't have to overthrow

1:19:27.640 --> 1:19:28.770
because you've got a strong arm,

1:19:28.770 --> 1:19:29.978
and don't worry about hitting anybody--

1:19:29.978 --> 1:19:33.690
- Coach, go have a seat, this game's over.

1:19:33.690 --> 1:19:35.123
(intense music)

1:19:35.123 --> 1:19:37.228
(John chuckles)

1:19:37.228 --> 1:19:38.311
- Go get 'em.

1:19:41.684 --> 1:19:45.017
(cheering and applause)

1:19:49.476 --> 1:19:52.309
- Just one, keep up your accuracy.

1:19:53.520 --> 1:19:54.830
Good pitch.

1:19:54.830 --> 1:19:55.830
- Bring it in, guys.

1:19:58.540 --> 1:20:01.533
Joey, the first one's coming to you, okay?

1:20:01.533 --> 1:20:04.334
- This kid's never been on a mound before,

1:20:04.334 --> 1:20:05.680
I want you stealing on the first pitch.

1:20:05.680 --> 1:20:07.506
He won't even look you back.

1:20:07.506 --> 1:20:08.756
- Okay, got it.

1:20:09.743 --> 1:20:14.743
- Look sharp!
(cheering and applause)

1:20:21.708 --> 1:20:22.791
Keep running.

1:20:26.076 --> 1:20:26.993
- He's out!

1:20:31.556 --> 1:20:34.723
- [Catcher] One down, play's to first.

1:20:42.807 --> 1:20:46.618
(indistinct chatter)

1:20:46.618 --> 1:20:47.978
- Come on now, Kyle,
show 'em what you got.

1:20:47.978 --> 1:20:49.492
- Sit 'em down!

1:20:49.492 --> 1:20:53.426
(cheering and applause)

1:20:53.426 --> 1:20:54.717
- Honey.
- Huh?

1:20:54.717 --> 1:20:55.800
- Watch this.

1:20:59.944 --> 1:21:03.027
(indistinct chatter)

1:21:12.956 --> 1:21:14.495
(cheering and applause)

1:21:14.495 --> 1:21:16.476
(upbeat music)

1:21:16.476 --> 1:21:17.916
- Throw that ball again, kid!

1:21:17.916 --> 1:21:19.616
Keep it up!

1:21:19.616 --> 1:21:23.466
- Go get the gun.

1:21:23.466 --> 1:21:24.299
Go get the gun.

1:21:24.299 --> 1:21:25.382
- Yeah, yeah.

1:21:40.548 --> 1:21:43.881
(cheering and applause)

1:21:57.038 --> 1:21:58.234
- Strike three.

1:21:58.234 --> 1:21:59.596
(cheering and applause)

1:21:59.596 --> 1:22:02.116
- Was that a knuckle curve?

1:22:02.116 --> 1:22:04.183
- [Catcher] That's two.

1:22:04.183 --> 1:22:07.683
- Did that kid just throw a knuckle curve?

1:22:08.559 --> 1:22:12.559
- [Announcer] Now batting,
number 53, AJ Garcia.

1:22:20.382 --> 1:22:21.215
- Cam.

1:22:44.374 --> 1:22:45.207
- Ball.

1:22:48.964 --> 1:22:50.652
(Ted chuckles)

1:22:50.652 --> 1:22:52.380
- What's he doing?

1:22:52.380 --> 1:22:55.630
- He's about to teach a bully a lesson.

1:22:56.927 --> 1:22:57.760
Hey.
- Hi.

1:23:00.039 --> 1:23:00.887
- Is he pitching?

1:23:00.887 --> 1:23:02.108
- Yeah.

1:23:02.108 --> 1:23:03.916
How'd it go?

1:23:03.916 --> 1:23:05.635
- I let up one.

1:23:05.635 --> 1:23:07.155
- Yeah.

1:23:07.155 --> 1:23:08.655
- What's he doing?

1:23:12.903 --> 1:23:15.236
- Ball four, take your base.

1:23:17.045 --> 1:23:22.045
- [Announcer] Now batting,
number 33, Mason Hastings.

1:23:24.130 --> 1:23:26.230
- That shiny new bat's not gonna help you.

1:23:27.666 --> 1:23:29.648
- You're the winning run, come on now.

1:23:29.648 --> 1:23:30.815
Let's rip one.

1:23:36.630 --> 1:23:38.965
- [Announcer] Looks like Cooke
is gonna stay in the windup

1:23:38.965 --> 1:23:41.058
and focus on the batter.

1:23:41.058 --> 1:23:43.558
(tense music)

1:23:54.018 --> 1:23:57.351
(cheering and applause)

1:23:59.320 --> 1:24:01.487
- You gotta be kidding me.

1:24:03.589 --> 1:24:05.468
- What the record for 12-year-old?

1:24:05.468 --> 1:24:06.968
- Well, it was 81.

1:24:07.900 --> 1:24:08.733
- Come on,

1:24:08.733 --> 1:24:12.536
get around early and drive
that fastball, come on!

1:24:12.536 --> 1:24:14.500
- That wasn't my fastball.

1:24:14.500 --> 1:24:15.950
Do you wanna see my fastball?

1:24:31.032 --> 1:24:31.865
(cheering and applause)

1:24:31.865 --> 1:24:32.698
- Strike.

1:24:39.208 --> 1:24:41.879
- Hey, this kid's superhuman.

1:24:41.879 --> 1:24:45.540
A 12-year-old arm cannot throw that hard.

1:24:45.540 --> 1:24:46.373
- Hey, Coach,

1:24:47.549 --> 1:24:50.080
how'd you like if he threw
that at your son's head?

1:24:52.421 --> 1:24:54.921
(tense music)

1:25:01.469 --> 1:25:03.621
- Come on, throw that again.

1:25:03.621 --> 1:25:05.270
- I can throw harder if you want.

1:25:05.270 --> 1:25:06.103
- Bring it on.

1:25:09.390 --> 1:25:10.640
- You ready for the heat?

1:25:15.709 --> 1:25:19.708
(cheering and applause)

1:25:19.708 --> 1:25:22.077
- Strike three!
(players celebrate)

1:25:22.077 --> 1:25:23.685
(cheering and applause)

1:25:23.685 --> 1:25:25.765
- (claps) Good game.

1:25:25.765 --> 1:25:29.034
(players celebrate)

1:25:29.034 --> 1:25:31.451
- [Players] Kyle! Kyle! Kyle!

1:25:33.301 --> 1:25:36.221
- [Announcer] Congratulations
to the Brighton All-Stars,

1:25:36.221 --> 1:25:39.482
our Connecticut state champions.

1:25:39.482 --> 1:25:42.806
The final score, Brighton
two, Oakwood one.

1:25:42.806 --> 1:25:46.520
Good luck at regionals,
boys, make us proud.

1:25:46.520 --> 1:25:51.520
(players celebrate)
(cheering and applause)

1:26:16.890 --> 1:26:17.723
- Hey, Ted,

1:26:20.630 --> 1:26:21.663
you got a second?

1:26:28.500 --> 1:26:29.540
- Hey, Chad.

1:26:29.540 --> 1:26:30.710
- Hey.

1:26:30.710 --> 1:26:31.543
Uh...

1:26:33.300 --> 1:26:34.170
I was...

1:26:35.880 --> 1:26:38.870
I was wrong not to give
Kyle a shot last year,

1:26:38.870 --> 1:26:40.653
him and a lotta other kids.

1:26:42.105 --> 1:26:42.938
(soft music)

1:26:42.938 --> 1:26:44.160
I'm really sorry about that.

1:26:45.630 --> 1:26:46.463
Your son,

1:26:47.810 --> 1:26:51.113
he's the greatest baseball
player I've ever seen, ever.

1:26:54.240 --> 1:26:55.200
- Listen, I...

1:26:56.930 --> 1:26:58.055
I'm sorry too.

1:26:58.055 --> 1:27:00.590
- No. (chuckles)
- I was, you know...

1:27:00.590 --> 1:27:02.653
Well, in a way, I should be thanking you.

1:27:04.175 --> 1:27:05.470
I don't think Kyle woulda worked that hard

1:27:05.470 --> 1:27:06.570
if he hadn't been cut.

1:27:08.390 --> 1:27:09.790
- Funny how things work out.

1:27:16.000 --> 1:27:17.225
- [Lou] Good game, Coach.

1:27:17.225 --> 1:27:18.058
- Thanks.

1:27:19.940 --> 1:27:22.633
- Excuse me, Mr. Cooke, Mrs. Cooke,

1:27:25.610 --> 1:27:26.490
I'm Lou Grey,

1:27:26.490 --> 1:27:27.390
I head up scouting

1:27:27.390 --> 1:27:29.860
for Stanford University's
baseball program.

1:27:29.860 --> 1:27:33.355
I'd like to talk to you about
your son if you have a moment.

1:27:33.355 --> 1:27:34.188
(Ted chuckles)

1:27:34.188 --> 1:27:36.380
- Isn't that some sort of,
uh, recruiting violation?

1:27:36.380 --> 1:27:39.071
I mean, Kyle's only
going into eighth grade.

1:27:39.071 --> 1:27:40.770
- (chuckles) Oh, no, no, no,

1:27:40.770 --> 1:27:42.820
I don't think Kyle's right for Stanford.

1:27:42.820 --> 1:27:44.300
This is about Xavier.

1:27:44.300 --> 1:27:46.310
Look, I caught a couple
of his games this week,

1:27:46.310 --> 1:27:47.930
and I think with a little
work on his breaking ball,

1:27:47.930 --> 1:27:49.927
and if his grades are good,

1:27:49.927 --> 1:27:50.760
I think we'd be interested

1:27:50.760 --> 1:27:53.120
in offering him a full scholarship.

1:27:53.120 --> 1:27:54.490
So you know,

1:27:54.490 --> 1:27:57.533
that's about a $300,000 investment
on our part in your son.

1:28:01.937 --> 1:28:03.510
Uh, alright, alright, look, (Ted chuckles)

1:28:03.510 --> 1:28:06.333
I realize this is coming
out of, well, left field.

1:28:07.830 --> 1:28:09.000
Here's my card,

1:28:09.000 --> 1:28:09.996
why don't you guys talk about it

1:28:09.996 --> 1:28:10.970
and give me a call in a day or two

1:28:10.970 --> 1:28:13.380
and maybe we can discuss
this further, alright?

1:28:13.380 --> 1:28:14.213
Pleasure meeting you.

1:28:14.213 --> 1:28:15.399
- Pleasure to meet you.

1:28:15.399 --> 1:28:16.972
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1:28:16.972 --> 1:28:18.732
Have a good day.

1:28:18.732 --> 1:28:20.830
- Uh, Mr. Grey,

1:28:20.830 --> 1:28:22.683
uh, just curious,

1:28:23.870 --> 1:28:26.313
why don't you think
Stanford's right for Kyle?

1:28:26.313 --> 1:28:28.220
(Lou chuckles)

1:28:28.220 --> 1:28:30.800
- Look, um, as a recruiting coach,

1:28:30.800 --> 1:28:32.630
I travel around the world all year long

1:28:32.630 --> 1:28:35.150
looking at young ballplayers, Mr. Cooke,

1:28:35.150 --> 1:28:37.410
there's no question in my mind
that in a couple of years,

1:28:37.410 --> 1:28:40.360
Kyle will be the number one
prospect on this entire planet.

1:28:41.210 --> 1:28:43.010
In fact, the day he graduates high school,

1:28:43.010 --> 1:28:45.040
some major league organization
will be offering you

1:28:45.040 --> 1:28:47.770
a hundred-million-dollar contract.

1:28:47.770 --> 1:28:49.670
Even Stanford can't compete with that.

1:28:50.740 --> 1:28:53.010
Look, um, I have to say this,

1:28:53.010 --> 1:28:53.843
obviously,

1:28:53.843 --> 1:28:55.803
you got a couple of great
ballplayers in your boys,

1:28:56.751 --> 1:28:57.584
from what I've seen,

1:28:57.584 --> 1:29:00.023
their interaction with
their coaches, teammates,

1:29:00.930 --> 1:29:03.093
you two have raised two fine young men.

1:29:03.940 --> 1:29:04.940
You should be proud.

1:29:06.092 --> 1:29:07.690
Well, look, I shouldn't
tie you up any longer.

1:29:07.690 --> 1:29:09.080
It's a pleasure meeting you.

1:29:09.080 --> 1:29:11.580
I look forward to talking some more.

1:29:11.580 --> 1:29:13.164
Have a great evening.

1:29:13.164 --> 1:29:14.831
Be well, my friends.

1:29:16.844 --> 1:29:19.261
(soft music)

1:30:08.925 --> 1:30:11.508
(upbeat music)

1:30:53.622 --> 1:30:56.205
(upbeat music)
